title Authentication Workflow

actor User
participant Browser
participant "Nginx\n(Reverse Proxy)" as Nginx
participant "Web App\n(React SPA)" as Web
participant "API\n(Node.js / Express)" as API
participant "Database\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB

note over Browser,DB: ── Initial Login ─────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Navigate to https://web.timekeeping.local
Browser->Nginx: GET / (HTTPS 443)
Nginx->Web: Proxy → web:3000
Web-->Browser: Render Login page

User->Browser: Enter email + password, click Login
Browser->Web: Submit form
Web->Web: Validate form (Zod)
Web->Nginx: POST https://api.timekeeping.local/v1/auth/login\n{ email, password }
Nginx->API: Rate-limited proxy → api:4000/v1/auth/login

API->API: Validate request body (Zod)
API->DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?
DB-->API: User record (with passwordHash)

API->API: bcrypt.compare(password, passwordHash) [cost=12]
note over API: Reject if compare fails → 401

API->API: Generate access token\nJWT HS256, payload={sub,email,role}\nExpires: 15 minutes
API->API: Generate refresh token\nJWT HS256, Expires: 7 days

API->API: bcrypt.hash(refreshToken) → hashedRefresh
API->DB: UPDATE users SET refreshToken=hashedRefresh,\nlastLoginAt=now() WHERE id=?
DB-->API: Updated

API-->Nginx: 200 OK\n{ accessToken, user: {id,email,role,firstName,lastName} }\nSet-Cookie: refreshToken=<jwt>; HttpOnly; Secure;\nSameSite=Strict; Max-Age=604800; Path=/v1/auth

Nginx-->Browser: 200 + body + Set-Cookie header
Browser->Web: Store accessToken in memory (NOT localStorage)
Web-->User: Redirect → Dashboard

note over Browser,DB: ── Authenticated API Request ─────────────────────

User->Browser: Navigate to Time Entries
Browser->Web: Route change
Web->Nginx: GET https://api.timekeeping.local/v1/time-entries\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>
Nginx->API: Proxy → api:4000
API->API: Verify JWT signature & expiry
API->DB: SELECT ... FROM time_entries WHERE userId=?
DB-->API: Entries
API-->Nginx: 200 + { data: [...], meta: {...} }
Nginx-->Browser: 200 + JSON
Web-->User: Render time entries

note over Browser,DB: ── Silent Token Refresh (access token expires) ────

Browser->Web: Axios interceptor catches 401
Web->Nginx: POST https://api.timekeeping.local/v1/auth/refresh\n(Cookie: refreshToken=<jwt> sent automatically)
Nginx->API: Rate-limited proxy → /v1/auth/refresh
API->API: Extract refresh token from cookie
API->API: Verify JWT signature & expiry
API->DB: SELECT refreshToken FROM users WHERE id=sub
DB-->API: Hashed refresh token
API->API: bcrypt.compare(tokenFromCookie, hashedFromDB)
note over API: Mismatch or expired → 401 (force re-login)

API->API: Rotate: generate new access token\n+ new refresh token
API->API: bcrypt.hash(newRefreshToken)
API->DB: UPDATE users SET refreshToken=newHash
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Nginx: 200 { accessToken }\nSet-Cookie: refreshToken=<newJwt>; HttpOnly; ...
Nginx-->Browser: New tokens
Web->Web: Retry original request with new accessToken

note over Browser,DB: ── Logout ─────────────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Click Logout
Browser->Web: Trigger logout
Web->Nginx: POST https://api.timekeeping.local/v1/auth/logout\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>
Nginx->API: Proxy
API->DB: UPDATE users SET refreshToken=NULL WHERE id=?
DB-->API: Cleared
API-->Nginx: 200 + Set-Cookie: refreshToken=; Max-Age=0
Nginx-->Browser: Cookie cleared
Web->Web: Clear accessToken from memory, clear React Query cache
Web-->User: Redirect → Login page
